  9  /-!
 10  # Isomorphisms
 11  
 12  This file defines isomorphisms between objects of a category.
 13  
 14  ## Main definitions
 15  
 16  - `structure iso` : a bundled isomorphism between two objects of a category;
 17  - `class is_iso` : an unbundled version of `iso`; note that `is_iso f` is usually *not* a `Prop`,
 18    because it holds the inverse morphism;
 19  - `as_iso` : convert from `is_iso` to `iso`;
 20  - `of_iso` : convert from `iso` to `is_iso`;
 21  - standard operations on isomorphisms (composition, inverse etc)
 22  
 23  ## Notations
 24  
 25  - `X ≅ Y` : same as `iso X Y`;
 26  - `α ≪≫ β` : composition of two isomorphisms; it is called `iso.trans`
 27  
 28  ## Tags
 29  
 30  category, category theory, isomorphism
 31  -/
 32  
 33  universes v u -- declare the `v`'s first; see `category_theory.category` for an explanation
